column5: My Navy and fishing buddy from Florida picks me up in Georgia on Wednesday the 31st. We'll take our time golfing along the way and be at our outfitters on the 7th for a fly in to Lake Wastayanipi on the 8th. We go to a different lake each year with a different outfitter. Only do fly-ins and never use live bait. Plugs and jigs and catch all the fish we want. Hope all of us have a good safe trip. Good luck. Go Navy!
26 days til Gullrock - Celebrating 15 years with a fishing trip.
2 days, 17 hours, 19 min 65 hours, 19 min 3919 min going to Dogtooth Lake, Ont, Walleye, here we come!!!!!!!!!!
1 day and a wake up how's the weather up there?
pine point resort
36 hours and we are headed to Wasbaskang for first time.1300 miles from TN to Wabaskang. Did I tell you I am excited? sidewinder
8 more days till I take the cross-lake ferry to Milwaulkee. Then drive all night (14 hrs) to Lac Seul. Then 7 more days till I can take a REAL shower. ME
3 days Watt Lake, ON
6 days until the annual 22 hour trip to the lower manitou. good friends, good fishing, and my two sons age 16 and 10. can't wait eric

12 days until we check in at Camp Lochalsh on the south end of Lake Wabatongushi (NE of Wawa, ON.) Fished a houseboat on Rainy Lake last summer with my 8 year old son, father, and grandfather. Only son and father are going this year. Treating the 2 of them to a float plane fly-in.
26 days and counting, 2 of us, to Abrams/Mimitaki, Tikinagan Camp been going for over 20 years.

Only 14 shopping days left til Christmas. My very first trip to Canada. June 9th-17th. I will be heading to Dogtooth Lake with my Hooters bowling buddies. (Hooters sponsors our bowling team) Seven days of walleye, smallmouth and northern heaven. Can't wait. I'm 50 years old and I feel like a kid at Chrismas. Joe

good for you blowhole..how come its taken you so long to get up here? thats right, life begins at 50!! lotw 1 week from today.have you guys seen how nice the weather is supposed to be the next couple of weeks!! outstanding. no labbats ice sitting for too long.. good luck fellas and stay safe jig out
12 long days to the 11 hr drive to Armstrong and and another 100 miles flight to Ogoki Lake. Good luck and Good fishin to all

I know there are other threads with this topic, but they're off the first page. How many days to your lake and what lake are you going to? 32 days to the Ogoki Reservoir with Mattice Lake Outfitters for me.
